awaitRegistrationAnswer

boolean awaitRegistrationAnswer(long timeout,
                                java.util.concurrent.TimeUnit unit)
                          throws java.lang.InterruptedException
Waits for an answer from the RTI to the registration request.

Parameters:
timeout - the maximum time to wait
unit - the time unit of the timeout argument.
Returns:
true if the we got a response from the RTI and false if the waiting time elapsed before the RTI sent a response.
Throws:
java.lang.InterruptedException - if the current thread is interrupted while waiting.
